{
  "doc_id": "47835",
  "text": "The phylogenetic tree comprised of 85 SSU reference sequences [CITATION_1] , two outgroup taxa, 30 AMF OTUs, and eight contigs (Fig 13) . Since the forward and reverse sequences were analysed separately, the same species could be represented by different OTUs. The 30 AMF OTUs were distributed as follows: 26 in Glomeraceae, two in Acaulosporaceae, one in Gigasporaceae, and one in Archaeosporaceae. The eight contigs were distributed as follows: three in Glomeraceae (3, 6, 7), two in Acaulosporaceae (2, 8), one in Gigasporaceae (4), one in Archaeosporaceae (5), and one in Diversisporaceae (1). None of the AMF reads were close to taxa within the Claroideoglomeraceae or Pacisporaceae.",
